STORY TIME : I was 18 when I first started modelling. I was studying fashion design in NIFT Bengaluru at the time. Growing up in vellore- I never thought modelling/ influencing was even a career option.

My 10 year plan was this: get my degree, get my masters, work for a designer and ultimately have my own label!

When I moved to Bangalore, my mind and heart opened up to the possibility of modelling when my seniors from college needed models to wear their garments for their assignments. 

My images somehow made their way to an agency ( that would later become my modelling agency). Life from then on changed but not completely- I still wanted to stick to my 10 year plan and make as much money as I could to help pay for masters. 

Then lockdown hit! 
I graduated during the lockdown and felt very stuck in my modelling career. I was only doing stereotypical brown girl shoots. Never any creative makeup or cool fashion. They saw my skin tone and could only see me in saris and lehengas. 

They could never imagine me shooting in a bikini because “ my knees and elbows were too dark” “my hips were too wide” 

I wanted to change that so badly. 

I started creating editorial makeup looks. I didn’t have any eyeliner, only paint and started drawing on my face. I remember how motivated and proud I was of myself and how I loved seeing myself like that. 

I invested in more makeup and began posting and posting every day that year. 

I started growing an audience of people who saw me and celebrated my work and I couldn’t have been more grateful.

Suddenly I felt a shift in my 10 year plan!!

I decided to take the leap and move to Mumbai! 
I was finally being booked for the kind of work I’ve always wanted to do!! 

Cut to now- I’m living the life of my dreams, travelling the world creating content and modelling for brands that 18 year old me could only dream about. 

Anyways long story short-
I’m so grateful for this life I’ve created and can’t wait for what’s in store next 🤍🧿
